subSubSection.paragraph:
Female (holotype) (Figs 
1-4
). Body length 4.7 mm, fore wing length 2.7 mm, ovipositor sheath 2.0 mm.

The paratype female (Figs 
5-8
) is identical to the holotype in all the characteristics described above except that it is darker than the holotype. The brownish patch in the midline of the upper face is larger and black; pronotum more reddish; the posterolateral dark patches of the mesoscutum are black; mesopleuron with less yellowish and more reddish colouration and almost black around the speculum; metanotum almost black; propodeum darker, the basal half black, apical half pale reddish; hind tibia darker brown in the middle; the first and second tergites are darker, the light edges of the apical tergites are slightly darker.
